cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper discusses random access protocols for communication systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions applications in the Internet of Things and machine-to-machine communication, which fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new protocol for contention resolution, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
